The Minister for Justice and Attorney-General of the Federation, Abubakar Chika Malami has hinted that very soon about sixty per cent of the opposition People’s Democratic Party ( PDP) members will defect to the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) in Kebbi State. Malami gave the hint at the Gesse hotel in Birnin Kebbi on Saturday during an interaction session with over 600 supporters in the state who gathered to affirm their support for him and Kebbi APC. The legal luminary who didnt mentions the names of the potential defectors added that deeper consultations have been made and contacts already established to bring them to the APC fold soon “my loyalty and support for APC and Bagudu still intact, I urge you all to obtain permanent voters cards (PVCs) and vote for APC come 2023.He call on all the associations to continue to support APC in Kebbi state and the nation at large, the gathering had in attendance top party echelons and top brass government officials.